INSERT INTO text_pages (`id`, `slug`, `title`, `description`, `content`, `type`, `comments_enabled`, `parent_id`) VALUES (4, 'privacy', 'Privacy Policy', '', '<p><b>Note: Tutorical and the tutorical.com domain are owned by Aeterna (<a href=\"http://aeternastudio.com\">aeternastudio.com</a>).</b></p>\n\n<p>This Privacy Policy (the “Policy”) sets out how Aeterna uses and protects any information that you provide when you use the Tutorical website. When used in the Policy, “we”, “us” and “our” refer to Aeterna; “site” and “website” refer to the information located at “http://tutorical.com”; “pages” refers to the information located on the various webpages on the tutorical.com domain.</p>\n\n<p>We are committed to ensuring that your privacy is protected. Should we ask you to provide certain information by which you can be identified when using our website, you can rest assured that it will only be used in accordance with the Policy. If you ever feel that your privacy has been compromised through this site, please contact us.</p>\n\n<h2>What we collect and how we use it</h2>\n\n<p>We use Google Analytics to monitor traffic onto our site. Google Analytics collects information anonymously. This information cannot be used by us to identify you personally. We use it to better understand how our visitors use our site in order to better their experience of it. Google Analytics collects the following information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Internet Protocol (IP) addresses;</li>\n	<li>pages visited on the site;</li>\n	<li>links clicked on the site;</li>\n	<li>how long site visitors stay;</li>\n	<li>domain names from which visitors connect to our site; and</li>\n	<li>search terms visitors use to reach our site if they arrived through a search engine</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If you use any forms on the site, (e.g. the contact form, the signup form), any information you type in is stored in our database. We do not provide this information to any 3rd parties. We may, however, use this information in an attempt to improve your experience of this site. For example, when you type your email to log in, we paste your email to the contact form to save you the step of having to re-type your email if you wish to contact us.</p>\n\n<p>If you provide your location through any form on the site (such as when entering your location while making your tutor profile), then that location is geocoded using Google Maps (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://maps.google.com\">maps.google.com</a>) to produce its latitude and longitude coordinates. These coordinates are used to place markers on various maps on the site, and for distance calculations on the search form. We also use these coordinates to derive the city and country of your location. However, the entered location is never revealed to anyone, and only an approximate location is shown on any maps on the site. We do not sell, reveal, or exchange this information with anyone other than Google (and then only to geocode it).</p>\n\n<h2>Security</h2>\n\n<p>We take security very seriously, and have placed many measures in place to ensure that your email and password are secure. Your email is only visible to you on your private account screen (<a href=\"http://tutorical.com/account\">tutorical.com/account</a>). Note that we do store it as plain text in our database. Your password, however, is salted and hashed using the phpass (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://openwall.com/phpass\">openwall.com/phpass</a>) password hashing framework. This means that your password is never visible to anyone, not even to us.</p>\n\n<h2>Cookies</h2>\n\n<p>We, like most websites, use cookies. Cookies are small pieces of information that allow web applications to respond to you as an individual. A web application can tailor its operations to your needs, likes and dislikes by gathering and remembering information about your preferences. We use cookies in the following three ways.</p>\n\n<p>We use cookies to record how you use the website. We use this to see overall which areas of the site are visited, which links are clicked, and which text is actually read. We use this information to better the website for our visitors and to strive to provide only relevant, useful information.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, while creating a tutor profile your information is saved in cookies. This is done for convenience (in case your browser is closed accidentally, any information you typed is not lost).</p>\n\n<p>Lastly, we have a number of social plugins that use cookies in compliance with their privacy policies. Please consult the following companies’ privacy policies to learn more:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Facebook (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://facebook.com\">facebook.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>Twitter (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://twitter.com\">twitter.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>Reddit (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://reddit.com\">reddit.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>Google (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://google.com\">google.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>AddThis (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://addthis.com\">addthis.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>DISQUS (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://disqus.com\">disqus.com</a>)</li>\n	<li>UserVoice (<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://uservoice.com\">uservoice.com</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>External Links</h2>\n\n<p>Our pages contain hyperlinks to external websites. These websites are subject to their own privacy policies that will likely differ from our own. We strive to ensure to only link to reputable companies and websites and ask you to please refer to their privacy policies for more information. We do not share any of your information with these or any external websites.</p>\n\n<p>On many pages, we provide user-created content (e.g. blog comments, tutor reviews, etc.) that may contain links to websites that we have not reviewed. While we strive to review all user-created content and respond quickly to any reports brought to our attention, we urge you to use discretion when opening external links.</p>\n\n<h2>About this Policy</h2>\n\n<p>The Policy is effective as of Feb 1, 2013. We reserve the right to change the Policy at any time. If we change it, we will post the then-current Policy on this page. Any changes to the Policy will be effective as of the day they are posted.</p>\n\n<h2>Questions and Comments</h2>\n\n<p>Please send any questions about our Privacy Policy to:</p>\n\n<p>\n<b>Andrei Khramtsov</b><br>\nTechnical Director, Co-Founder<br>\n<a href=\"mailto:andrei@aeternastudio.com\">andrei@aeternastudio.com</a>\n</p>', 'regular', 0, 0);
INSERT INTO text_pages (`id`, `slug`, `title`, `description`, `content`, `type`, `comments_enabled`, `parent_id`) VALUES (5, 'credits', 'Credits', 'List of others\' code snippets, plugins, extensions, libraries, and websites that were used in the making of Tutorical.', '			<div class=\"small-width-content\">\r\n				<p>Tutorical was built by <a href=\"http://aeternastudio.com\">Aeterna</a>, but we used a lot of code snippets, plugins, extensions, libraries, and websites that were made by other hard-working designers and programmers (often times for free). They\'re listed below:</p>\r\n\r\n				<h4>CSS</h4>			\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://css-tricks.com/snippets/css/clear-fix/\">Clearfix by Chris Coyier (CSS-Tricks)</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://meyerweb.com/eric/tools/css/reset/\">Eric Meyer\'s CSS Reset</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://lesscss.org/\">LESS</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://lesshat.com/\">LESS Hat</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://wearekiss.com/simpless\">SimpLESS</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://ryanfait.com/resources/footer-stick-to-bottom-of-page/\">Sticky Footer by Ryan Fait</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://winless.org/\">WinLess</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n\r\n				<h4>JavaScript</h4>			\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.addthis.com/\">AddThis</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://harvesthq.github.io/chosen/\">Chosen</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2855865/jquery-regex-validation-of-e-mail-address\">Email validation function (JavaScript) by aSeptik</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.google.com/analytics/\">Google Analytics</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://deepliquid.com/content/Jcrop.html\">Jcrop</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://jquery.com/\">Jquery</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://jqueryui.com/\">Jquery UI</a> (what would life be without them?)</li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://labs.abeautifulsite.net/jquery-dropdown/\">Jquery Bootstrap-Style Dropdown</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/jquery-textfill/jquery-textfill\">Jquery TextFill</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.jacklmoore.com/autosize/\">Jquery Autosize by Jack Moore</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/mathiasbynens/jquery-placeholder\">Jquery Placeholder</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/douglascrockford/JSON-js\">JSON in JavaScript by Douglas Crockford</a>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/Kicksend/mailcheck\">Mailcheck</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://phpjs.org/functions/nl2br/\">nl2br (JavaScript) from php.js</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://needim.github.io/noty/\">Noty Jquery Notifications</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://foundation.zurb.com/docs/components/reveal.html\">Reveal Modal from Foundation by Zurb</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://ivaynberg.github.io/select2/\">Select2</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://selectivizr.com/\">selectivizr</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://unwrongest.com/projects/show-password/\">Show Password</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://unwrongest.com/projects/password-strength/\">Password Strength</a> by Jan Jarfalk</li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://ejohn.org/blog/title-capitalization-in-javascript/\">TitleCase (JavaScript) by John Resig</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n\r\n				<h4>PHP</h4>			\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://ellislab.com/codeigniter\">CodeIgniter Framework</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://github.com/EllisLab/CodeIgniter/issues/446#issuecomment-11059869\">CodeIgniter is_money function by Antonio Macs</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.zachstronaut.com/posts/2009/01/20/php-relative-date-time-string.html\">Relative date/time strings function by Zachary Johnson</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.white-hat-web-design.co.uk/blog/resizing-images-with-php/\">Simple Image PHP Class</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://konyukhov.com/soft/tank_auth/\">Tank Auth Library</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://camendesign.com/code/title-case\">TitleCase (PHP) by Kroc Camen</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.uploadify.com/\">Uploadify</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				\r\n				<h4>Websites</h4>\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.charactercountonline.com/\">Character Count Tool</a></li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://stackexchange.com/\">Stack Exchange Sites</a> (mainly <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://ux.stackexchange.com/\">UX</a> and <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/\">Stack Overflow</a>)</li>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://workflowy.com/\">Workflowy</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n\r\n				<h4>Misc</h4>\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.glyphish.com/\">Glyphish Icons</a></li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n				\r\n				<div class=\"centered\">\r\n					<div class=\"boxes standard\">\r\n						<p>If we forgot to mention your contribution to Tutorical, <a href=\"http://tutorical.com/contact\" data-reveal-id=\"contact-modal\">get in touch</a> and we\'ll add you to the list.</p>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n			</div>', 'regular', 0, 0);
INSERT INTO text_pages (`id`, `slug`, `title`, `description`, `content`, `type`, `comments_enabled`, `parent_id`) VALUES (6, 'sitemap', 'Sitemap', '', '<div class=\"small-width-content\">\n				<p>A sitemap lists all the publicly accessible pages (i.e. those that you don\'t need to log in to see) on a site. It doesn\'t list pages with changing content though (e.g. tutor profiles, request details, and so on...).</p>\n\n				<h4>Tutorical</h4>\n				<ul>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/\">Home</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/about\">About</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/contact\">Contact</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/sitemap\">Sitemap</a> <span class=\"tiny-aftertext\">(you are here!)</span></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/credits\">Credits</a></li>				\n				</ul>\n\n				<h4>Requests and Tutors</h4>\n				<ul>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/requests/new-request\">Make a Tutor Request</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/find\">Find a Tutor</a></li>\n\n				</ul>\n\n				<h4>Account</h4>			\n				<ul>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/login\">Login</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/signup/tutor\">Become a Tutor</a></li>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/signup/student\">Become a Student</a></li>\n				</ul>\n\n				<h4>Legal</h4>\n				<ul>\n					<li><a href=\"http://tutorical.com/privacy\">Privacy Policy</a></li>				\n				</ul>\n			</div>', 'regular', 0, 0);
INSERT INTO text_pages (`id`, `slug`, `title`, `description`, `content`, `type`, `comments_enabled`, `parent_id`) VALUES (7, 'about', 'About Tutorical', '', '<p>Tutorical is a place where students can find tutors near them, and tutors can advertise their services.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Tidbits</h2>\r\n<div id=\"about-item-cont\">\r\n	<div class=\"about-items left\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/profile.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">Detailed Tutor Profiles</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">Tutors can specify when they can tutor, where they can meet, what they charge (hourly, range, or free), and many other details about themselves.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"about-items\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/reviews.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">Multi-Part Reviews</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">Students can read/write descriptions of their tutoring sessions and review tutors\' expertise, helpfulness, response, and clarity.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"about-items left\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/money.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">Free Service</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">Unlike traditional tutoring companies, we don\'t take a cut of tutors\' profits and we don\'t charge students anything for using our service.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"about-items left\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/students.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">Students/Tutors Management</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">Tutors and students can accept, reject, review, and manage their contacts quickly and easily from their account.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"about-items left\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/request.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">For Students: Tutor Requests</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">Type a subject, location, and max price and let tutors come to you! Read their offers, check out their profiles, and find your perfect match.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n\r\n	<div class=\"about-items\">\r\n		<img class=\"about-item-images\" src=\"http://tutorical.com/assets/images/about/marketing.jpg\">\r\n		<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-titles\">For Tutors: Marketing Tools</span>\r\n			<span class=\"about-item-text\">From the Marketing page on your account, advertise your profile through social media and use snippets to post to classifieds sites like Craigslist.</span>\r\n		</div>\r\n	</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h2>When, Where, and Who</h2>\r\n<p>Tutorical was launched in January 2013 from the Great Canadian North. It\'s managed by Andrei Khramtsov of <a href=\"http://aeternastudio\">Aeterna</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Get in Touch</h2>\r\n<p>For general comments and questions, please visit our <a href=\"http://tutorical.com/contact\" data-reveal=\"contact-modal\">contact page</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For press inquiries, please contact:<br>\r\n	<span id=\"press-contact-info\">\r\n		<span class=\"press-contact-info\"><b>Andrei Khramtsov</b></span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"press-contact-info\">Technical Director</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"press-contact-info\"><a href=\"mailto:andrei@aeternastudio.com\">andrei@aeternastudio.com</a></span>\r\n	</span>\r\n</p>', 'regular', 0, 0);
