INSERT INTO wp_posts (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES (17, 1, '2013-07-02 04:32:28', '2013-07-02 04:32:28', 'Learning a language is hard work, and it\'s made even harder when you\'re learning a language that has very limited free online resources. Such is the case with Hindi - a language that gramatically is pretty easy (compared to more commonly studied languages like Spanish and German), but is difficult to learn simply because there\'s not much to learn from.\n\nThen there\'s <em><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info\" target=\"_blank\">hindilanguage.info</a></em>. Run by <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/about/\" target=\"_blank\">David Templin</a>, it\'s a fantastic free online Hindi language resource. If you\'ve taken on the daunting task of learning this language, then you have check it out.\n<h2>5 Reasons it rocks</h2>\n<h3>1. In-Depth Grammar Articles</h3>\nNo website has a more thorough analysis of <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/hindi-grammar/\" target=\"_blank\">Hindi grammar</a> than <em>hindilanguage.info</em>. Nouns, verbs, syntax, particles, conditional sentences, etc; pretty much every grammatical corner of the language is covered.\n\n<strong>Just watch out</strong>: David really knows his stuff, to the point where you might find yourself having to research some of the grammatical jargon he uses (e.g. \"<a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/hindi-grammar/postpositions/ko/\" target=\"_blank\">kataphoric references</a>\"). But trust me, it\'s worth it. These grammar articles might seem a bit dry at times, but they\'ll help you jump the hump from being \'so-so\' at Hindi to attaining true fluency.\n<h3>2. Hindi Script Transcriptions</h3>\nPart of the difficulty in for Westerners learning the language is that it\'s so foreign to the ears. There are 4 different t\'s and d\'s, 3-4 r\'s, and many sounds that aren\'t easy for us to pick up on. Watching a Hindi show and trying to understand what people are saying would be a lot easier if there were Hindi subtitles (which are near impossible to find).\n\nThankfully, David\'s taken it on himself to write <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/transcripts/\" target=\"_blank\">transcripts</a> of popular Hindi serials and to let us read them at no cost. Check out his latest work (as of June 2013) - an episode of <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/transcripts/sarabhai-vs-sarabhai/episode-7-indravadan-goes-missing/\" target=\"_blank\">Sarabhai vs Sarabhai</a>.\n\nThe only downside is that this section of his site is a work-in-progress, with currently only 2 transcriptions available.\n<h3>3. Q&amp;A</h3>\nGot a question about Hindi? <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/q-and-a/\" target=\"_blank\">Just ask!</a> David\'s very knowledgeable about the language, and has many of his own resources in case he doesn\'t have an answer right away. His answers, just like his articles, are very detailed and informative.\n\nSome topics he\'s covered:\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/q-and-a/the-various-words-for-but/\" target=\"_blank\">The Various Words for “But”</a>,</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/q-and-a/mat-nahin-and-na/\" target=\"_blank\">मत, नहीं, and न</a>, and</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/q-and-a/kaun-hai-versus-kaun-hota-hai/\" target=\"_blank\">कौन है versus कौन होता है</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>4. Notes</h3>\nHindi\'s an odd language. There are sentence configurations that just don\'t translate well into English, or words that have multiple subtle meanings, and so on. David has (as of June 2013) <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/\" target=\"_blank\">3 free online volumes of notes</a> on miscellaneous Hindi oddities like:\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-3/common-word-order-variations/\" target=\"_blank\">Common Word Order Variations</a>,</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-3/contrafactual-sentences/\" target=\"_blank\">Contrafactual Sentences</a>, and</li>\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-2/jaise-ki/\" target=\"_blank\">जैसे कि</a></li>\n</ul>\nThese are short, jargon-free, easy-to-read pieces that can clear up many misconceptions and misunderstandings you might have about the language.\n<h3>5. Dialogs</h3>\nThis is a small section with some big potential. David\'s scripted out a simple scene, translated each line, and analyzed it with an analysis that\'s four times as long as the dialog itself. And then, to top it off, he added an exercise section underneath it. I mean, wow! Just a thank you doesn\'t cut it; <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/dialogs/dialog-1/\">you\'ve gotta check it out</a>.\n\nBut, like with the transcripts, this is still a limited section with (for now) only one dialog available.\n<h2>The one fuss...</h2>\nWhile <em>hindilanguage.info</em> is a fantastic reference, its lesson-by-lesson section is still in development (<a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/lessons/lesson-1-introduction-to-devanagari/\">currently there is one lesson</a>). If you\'d like an full start-to-finish Hindi guide, then you won\'t find it here yet<em>.</em>If you\'d prefer a more direct approach, I (with a whole lotta bias) recommend you use <a href=\"http://tutorical.com/\">Tutorical</a> to find Hindi tutors near you.\n\nIn either case: subscribe to <em>hindilanguage.info\'s</em> mailing list. It\'s a great supplement to any Hindi lessons/books/classes you might be using.\n<h2>Disclaimer</h2>\nAnother branch of our company - <a href=\"http://aeternastudio.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Aeterna Studio</a> - worked on the redesign of <em>hindilanguage.info</em> site. Nevertheless, we consider it to be an incredible Hindi language resource, and a good online alternative to a local Hindi tutor.', 'Hindi Language Resource Review - hindilanguage.info', 'hindilanguage.info is a fantastic free online Hindi language resource. If you\'ve taken on the daunting task of learning this language, then you have to check it out.', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'aenean-at-ultricies-purus-rhoncus-eleifend-dolor', '', '', '2013-07-24 10:26:19', '2013-07-24 10:26:19', '', 0, 'http://localhost/Software/Tutorical/trunk/blog/?p=17', 0, 'post', '', 0);
