ndi oddities like:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-3/common-word-order-variations/\" target=\"_blank\">Common Word Order Variations</a>,</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-3/contrafactual-sentences/\" target=\"_blank\">Contrafactual Sentences</a>, and</li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/notes/volume-2/jaise-ki/\" target=\"_blank\">जैसे कि</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese are short, jargon-free, easy-to-read pieces that can clear up many misconceptions and misunderstandings you might have about the language.\r\n<h3>5. Dialogs</h3>\r\nThis is a small section with some big potential. David\'s scripted out a simple scene, translated each line, and analyzed it with an analysis that\'s four times as long as the dialog itself. And then, to top it off, he added an exercise section underneath it. I mean, wow! Just a thank you doesn\'t cut it; <a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/dialogs/dialog-1/\">you\'ve gotta check it out</a>.\r\n\r\nBut, like with the transcripts, this is still a limited section with (for now) only one dialog available.\r\n<h2>The one fuss...</h2>\r\nWhile <em>hindilanguage.info</em> is a fantastic reference, its lesson-by-lesson section is still in development (<a href=\"http://hindilanguage.info/lessons/lesson-1-introduction-to-devanagari/\">currently there is one lesson</a>). If you\'d like an full start-to-finish Hindi guide, then you won\'t find it here yet<em>.</em>If you\'d prefer a more direct approach, I (with a whole lotta bias) recommend you use <a href=\"http://tutorical.com/\">Tutorical</a> to find Hindi tutors near you.\r\n\r\nIn either case: subscribe to <em>hindilanguage.info\'s</em> mailing list. It\'s a great supplement to any Hindi lessons/books/classes you might be using.\r\n<h2>Disclaimer</h2>\r\nAnother branch of our company - <a href=\"http://aeternastudio.com/\">Aeterna Studio</a> - worked on the redesign of <em>hindilanguage.info</em> site. Nevertheless, we consider it to be an incredible Hindi language resource, and a good online alternative to a local Hindi tutor.', 'Hindi Language Resource Review - hindilanguage.info', 'hindilanguage.info is a fantastic free online Hindi language resource. If you\'ve taken on the daunting task of learning this language, then you have to check it out.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '17-revision-21', '', '', '2013-07-04 16:43:32', '2013-07-04 16:43:32', '', 17, 'http://localhost/Software/Tutorical/trunk/blog/tutorical/17-revision-21', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
